  "text": "The HTTP connection manager route matching in Envoy is implemented across a small set of core files:\n\n1. **`source/common/router/config_impl.h` / `config_impl.cc`** \u2014 This is the primary implementation. It contains:\n   - `ConfigImpl` \u2014 the top-level route configuration that delegates to `RouteMatcher`\n   - `RouteMatcher` \u2014 implements `findVirtualHost()` (virtual host selection by `:authority`/Host header, including exact match, wildcard suffix/prefix match, and default vhost) and `route()` which chains vhost selection \u2192 route matching\n   - `VirtualHostImpl` \u2014 implements `getRouteFromEntries()` which iterates route entries and calls `matches()` on each\n   - Route entry implementations (`PrefixRouteEntryImpl`, `PathRouteEntryImpl`, `RegexRouteEntryImpl`, `ConnectRouteEntryImpl`, `PathSeparatedPrefixRouteEntryImpl`, `UriTemplateMatcherRouteEntryImpl`) \u2014 each implements `matches()` for its match type\n   - `RouteEntryImplBase` \u2014 base class containing route action configuration (cluster selection, timeouts, retries, hedging, hash policy, weighted clusters, header manipulation, etc.)\n\n2. **`source/common/http/conn_manager_impl.h` / `conn_manager_impl.cc`** \u2014 The HTTP connection manager's `ActiveStream` calls `refreshCachedRoute()` which snaps the route config and calls `snapped_route_config_->route()`, then `setRoute()` to cache the result. This is the entry point that triggers route matching during request processing.\n\n3. **`source/common/router/scoped_config_impl.h` / `scoped_config_impl.cc`** \u2014 Implements `ScopedConfigImpl::getRouteConfig()` for scoped routing, selecting the appropriate route configuration based on scope keys before virtual host matching.\n\n4. **`source/common/router/delegating_route_impl.h` / `delegating_route_impl.cc`** \u2014 `DelegatingRoute` and `DelegatingRouteEntry` wrapper classes that allow filters to override route properties while delegating to the original matched route.",
